  "text": "DrugBank and KEGG databases were parsed using the Perl library libwww-perl. OpenBabel [CITATION_1] was used to obtain Tanimoto scores, further analysis was done using R. A script written in Perl was employed to loop over entire procedure using 1000 random drug-metabolite pairs (bootstrapping).",
